items.text: Great food, generous portions. Disappointing service, forgot to bring our coffee even after asking multiple times.
The Full Melba breakfast is excellent. Slow service.
Love the simple brunch menu but service can be slow
Nice ambience, but the food can be better. Great for couple time.  They also do events,as there was a birthday party just outside with a blown up bouncy castle.
Less than 10 ppl in the cafe and staff questioned why I want to take a 4 seater. still managed to serve syrup with ant in it. Truffle fries nice but not great. Incompetent staff
Great truffle fries & BLT
Caesar salad is bland. 3 Little Pigs pizza taste as good as the frozen stuff I get from supermarket as emergency standbys.
Great decor, average fare. Love the interior and furnishing, but the food in isolation is absolutely nothing special. The b.l.a.t sarnie was one-dimensional, flavorless bacon.
good coffee, portabello mushroom was sweet!
Wait staff ranges from being friendly and helpful to downright slow and clueless. Dreadful. Only consolation is the well-managed and efficient kitchen. Not worth second visit.
Best carrot cake in singapore IMO
Love the coffee here
Another awesome place to chill out. Nice ambiance and great food! Give their thin crust pizzas a try. And also if you are lucky enough, you may enjoy a free outdoor live arts performance too!
Almost everything!
Don't come here unless you have lots of time, not thirsty and not hungry! Service is bad. Staff are not trained properly and there is no system in place. Won't blame the staff.
Come before 10am to avoid queue for seats. Service is very slow and forgetful during peak periods.
Great ambience, lots of space, not noisy like some of the other brunch places, service was really good
Crayfish linguini. Pretty awesome tasting dish.
They open early on weekends (8.30) and there's a huge field and gravel pit and bouncy castles set up right next to al fresco tables. Yay for tired parents of toddlers!
I've been here 5 times & have tried 16 dishes. LOVED: 1) Truffle Fries 2) The Melba Burger (180g, Bacon, Cheese). FAILED: Rocket Salad (w Sun-dried Tomatoes). See Top 10 dishes on Foodmento:
kids can play, decent brunch... the burgers and pizza are yummy, too
Loved the chili crab pizza, and coke float. Crap music. Tad on the pricey side but nice ambience
I find it quite expensive considering the location. The crayfish pasta and piggy pizza is yums.
Try to be early to beat the crowd.
French fries too salty!
Pet-friendly cafe so bring your doggies and sit at the patio. There's a huge field for kids and dogs to burn off energy too.
Nice Truffle fries and Cafe Melba Pizza is yummilicous. A family orientated + kid friendly place - Weekend have bouncy castle out on the open field right in front of the cafe.
Food quality is going down. Charged $1 extra for a $8 juice without ice, Guys its not a food court, you re charging premium anyways. Also $3 extra for salmon for $18 eggs Benedict. Cheap tricks!
High prices: Terribly expensive for such a non-central, tucked-away spot. With taxes, fish & chips $28! (20% cheaper & tastier @ Greenwood Fish Mkt), eggs Benedict $21, regular rootbeer float $12!!
Eggs benedict was done well, like Australian standards. Probably will not return because there's a severe lack of appetizing desserts.
To say service is lax - ordered a Mocha that didn't arrive and after THREE times asking still didn't arrive. Fourth time and tell me it wasn't in the orders.
Credit must be given to the chefs in the kitchen - they've a better team than the front of house.
Sad that it is no longer pet friendly. Need to get a proper license. Why can Spore be more inclusive n tolerant as a society towards pets and pple! Sigh
3 little pigs pizza. every bite makes u want more. lovely.
Are you sure this is freshly squeeze juice?? :/
Kids friendly.
Great Truffle Fries
Poor service. Rosti is delicious.

Service staff seemed confused. My eggs florentine were ok but the spinach was over cooked and too oily. And one cherry tomato, really? The muffin was nice and soft though.  Not sure if I'll come back.
Симпатичное заведение. Приятное обслуживание. Хорошее меню. Уютно.
Nice chill out place at the end of Goodman Road.
Perfect place for lunch and a couple of drinks with friends. Kids love it too, with the big field and bouncy castle.
All day bfast all the way! Hashbrown, plum tomatoe, sausage, bacon, egg, beans, loaf....no greens!
Really good music here, shame the road is so noisy :-/ despite that, I still love coming here for their great selection of food and drinks! My personal fave: all day breakfast!
Service here really SUCKS big time! they didn't serve the ice-cream for the two kids' meals and when I asked about it with the check, waitress said curtly it's because I didn't ask. Slow & rude!
Portabello mushroom salad! Great taste:)
You can actually enter by the side gate so bus stop @ Mountbatten road is easier access then going from goodman road
Eggs ben was nice. I thought the eggs were fresh. Bacon was yummy. I liked the lasagna too & Melba breakfast set was good. It was a busy Sunday brunch but over-all I would give it a 4 out of 5 stars.
The eggs benny was ok. But serving a ristretto when an espresso is ordered and not knowing the difference is not. Also: generally incompetent service.
Chicken parmigiana

Service can be improved. Staff has no food knowledge when asked. Worse yet, chef takes no pride in telling service staff the difference between the hanger steak and rib eye. Had to self google myself.
The ambience
Melba redamg beef is super tender & flavorful
It's true what people say about the horrible service, sour faces abound.
Spacious, quiet , reasonable price
Nice dining outdoor but the service is atrocious! Had to go up a couple of times to get missing items and get a server to serve us.
Mixed leaves salad. Normal. U & I can make better.
Try out the passion fruit cake it's fantastic
Great environment, good coffee, decent food. Kids dine for free promo is on right now.
The rendang is tasty! Coffee is up to standard too.
Fantastic environment, great staff, pizza is great
Great environment, terribly lax service
Mediocre food and service. However location is ideal and it's a nice place to chill. Easy parking!
Family friendly restaurant. They have tons of baby seats plus a bouncy castle for kids to play in.
Rosti is pretty good, but gets a bit chewy when cold. The poached eggs are cold and tasteless which is strange. Love the flat white. And good for kids cause there's a bouncy castle and kids soccer.
All day breakfast served here & here's medium rare steak with wedges and two poached eggs $29.00 ( price a bit steep ) but nice ambience, away from crowded cafes in town  ..
Great for kids; food is good but not memorable. It gets super busy after 10:30am on Sundays. They don't take reservation unless it's for dinner.
Brunch only on weekends and PH. Eggs and pancakes are good!!
Pizza bread basket with homemade dips. This one is good.
Good mixed of seasoning - penne carbonara.
Eggs Benedict is my fave. Light and oh so delish!
Want smth sweet to end your meal with? Order the strawberry with Horlick liquid dessert! It's soooo good it's like walking into a fluffy cloud and eating like it's cotton candy.
Clean, bright, lovely place. Three pigs pizza was delish.
I always go for the brunch menu. Pancakes and Eggs Benedict!
